Updated `content/papers/radiative.effects.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

Concise summary of changes:
- Added KaTeX equation numbering tags so all in-text equation references now resolve to visible numbered display equations (including Appendix labels like `A2`, `A5`, `B1`, `B2`).
- Split multi-part referenced equations into individually tagged displays where needed (`24a`/`24b`/`24c`, `27a`/`27b`/`27c`, `33a`/`33b`/`33c`) to match prose references.
- Normalized two inline superscript citations to footnote citation format:
  - `Herzberg$^{11}$` -> `Herzberg[^11]`
  - `Uehling,$^{7}$` -> `Uehling,[^7]`
- Added one missing paragraph break between sentences in the Lamb-shift discussion.
- Updated one prose reference from `Eqs. (24)` to `Eqs. (24a)-(24c)` for consistency with explicit equation numbering.

Self-check completed:
- Paragraph breaks requiring separation are blank-line separated.
- No unresolved in-text Eq references to missing display-equation numbers remain.
